(80, 1, '2014-10-22 19:53:04', '2014-10-22 19:53:04', '<p>RIBA</p>\r\n<p>Matt has been working with the team since August 2013 bringing over 13 years’ experience in the successful design and delivery of healthcare projects. With specific expertise in the design of acute and mental health developments, Matt has been heavily involved in the client and user group consultation process. Outside of work, Matt enjoys fell running and trying to stay afloat in his dinghy. He is also a member of the Holmfirth Transition Town sustainability group and has been a governor at his children’s school for the last four years.</p>', 'Matt Cromack', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'matt-cromack', '', '', '2014-11-11 11:02:09', '2014-11-11 11:02:09', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=people&#038;p=80', 0, 'people', '', 0),
(81, 1, '2014-10-22 19:53:34', '2014-10-22 19:53:34', '<p>BA (Hons) Dip. Arch Dip RIBA</p>\r\n<p>Steve co-founded Bowman Riley Healthcare with Mark Dean bringing over 17 years’ experience of designing healthcare buildings. He manages a specialist healthcare design team delivering a large number of complex and challenging projects varying from hospitals to medical centres and aged care facilities. A UK Board member of IHEEM, he has particular expertise in strategic and master planning, user group consultation and concept design development. Steve is a founder member of the Health Information Model steering group for Health BIM. He is also a director of Bowman Riley Innovate, the company’s research and development division. Out of work interests are life drawing, DIY and studying the benefits of eating chocolate!</p>', 'Steve Batson', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'steve-batson', '', '', '2014-11-11 11:01:09', '2014-11-11 11:01:09', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=people&#038;p=81', 0, 'people', '', 0),
(82, 1, '2014-10-22 19:53:45', '2014-10-22 19:53:45', '<p>Dip. Arch.</p>\r\n<p>Tim joined Bowman Riley Architects in April 2010. His previous experience is predominantly in the healthcare sector, where until recently he was a director in a healthcare architects practice. His experience as an architect also encompasses work in the blue light sector, project management and conservation</p>', 'Tim Smith', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tim-smith', '', '', '2014-11-11 11:00:01', '2014-11-11 11:00:01', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=people&#038;p=82', 0, 'people', '', 0),
(83, 1, '2014-10-22 19:54:06', '2014-10-22 19:54:06', '<p>BA (Hons), MCIM</p>\r\n<p>Samantha joined the practice in 2011 with ten years’ experience of marketing in the construction industry having previously worked for Turner &amp; Townsend and Atkins. She works alongside the directors to provide marketing, communications and business development expertise. Samantha enjoys the arts, cycling, travel and is an advanced scuba diver.</p>', 'Samantha Jevons', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'john-smith-6', '', '', '2014-11-11 10:58:24', '2014-11-11 10:58:24', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=people&#038;p=83', 0, 'people', '', 0),
(84, 1, '2014-10-22 19:54:12', '2014-10-22 19:54:12', '<p>BA(Hons) Dip Arch Post Grad Dip.</p>\r\n<p>Stephen was promoted to Associate in 2008 and leads part of the retail team focusing on the design and delivery of new build projects. His team secured the first BREEAM Excellent 2006 accredited supermarket in the UK. Stephen also coordinates our BIM implementation strategy ensuring that the practice remains at the forefront of this field.  Outside work, Stephen is a member of Ilkley and District Round Table and as former Chair enjoys taking time out to raise money for local charities when he is not chasing after his young family.</p>', 'Stephen Haestier', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'stephen-haestier', '', '', '2014-11-11 10:58:03', '2014-11-11 10:58:03', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=people&#038;p=84', 0, 'people', '', 0),
(85, 1, '2014-10-22 19:54:15', '2014-10-22 19:54:15', '<p>BA (Hons), Dip Arch, RIBA</p>\r\n<p>Steve joined Bowman Riley in 1994 and was promoted to Associate in 1999. For the past decade he has specialised in retail and commercial developments pioneering fast track delivery, sustainable construction and zero carbon technologies. Steve has more recently been responsible for the delivery of a number of large extension projects, requiring complex phasing solutions, and shell fit outs for a leading supermarket chain. Outside of work, Steve enjoys playing the drums, ten pin bowling and family walks.</p>', 'Steve McDonald', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'john-smith-4', '', '', '2014-11-11 10:57:19', '2014-11-11 10:57:19', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=people&#038;p=85', 0, 'people', '', 0),
(86, 1, '2014-10-22 19:54:17', '2014-10-22 19:54:17', '<p>BA (Hons), BSc (Hons)</p>\r\n<p>With over 10 years’ experience, Tom is a qualified interior designer and architectural technologist. He has been involved in a variety of schemes from design concept through specification and design development to delivery and successful completion. Tom loves cycling and renovating his self-designed home.</p>', 'Tom Shelley', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'john-smith-3', '', '', '2014-11-11 10:47:39', '2014-11-11 10:47:39', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=people&#038;p=86', 0, 'people', '', 0),
(87, 1, '2014-10-22 19:54:19', '2014-10-22 19:54:19', '<p>Promoted to Associate in 2013, Andrew manages projects in the commercial, hotel and leisure, social and private housing sectors. His experience covers all aspects of project delivery from inception through to completion but his main skills lie in developing design concepts up to planning stage. Andrew’s current role involves leading a team to deliver a £20m new HQ office building in Leeds. Out of work, Andrew likes mountain biking, snowboarding, live music and cooking/eating good food.</p>', 'Andrew Wolstenholme', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'andrew-wolstenholme', '', '', '2014-11-11 10:47:13', '2014-11-11 10:47:13', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=people&#038;p=87', 0, 'people', '', 0),
