(351, 1, '2014-10-29 19:27:24', '2014-10-29 19:27:24', '<h1>Estate Rationalisation</h1>\r\n<p class="p1"><span class="s1">As part of the UK Government’s Smart Cities drive to make sure the UK is leading the global race to develop smarter cities, the efficiency and productivity of property is of increasing importance.  Property asset-led transformation has the potential to generate significant savings and be a catalyst for wider organisational change.</span></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Bowman Riley Innovate brings a distinctive combination of skills, knowledge and experience to support clients in improving the performance of estates through considered strategies.</span></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><span class="s1">We can harness the opportunities presented by Building Information Modelling (BIM), big data, laser scanning and data storage to provide new innovative ways of providing evidence-based information about the assets of an organisation.  We produce estate business plans following analysis of data, which can be used to proactively influence senior management decision making to ultimately improve the performance and efficiency of an estate.</span></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><span class="s1">The optimisation, use and rationalisation of entire estates or single assets is achieved for a range of clients for the benefit of the business, with clear weighted prioritisation programmes developed for short and long term capital and operational revenue returns.</span></p>\r\n<p class="p1">We also offer a range of building consultancy services around estates rationalisation, to find out more visit our Building Consultancy services.</p>', 'Estate Rationalisation', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'estate-rationalisation', '', '', '2014-11-06 14:55:52', '2014-11-06 14:55:52', '', 338, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?page_id=351', 5, 'page', '', 0),
