(402, 1, '2014-10-29 21:11:23', '2014-10-29 21:11:23', '<p>The Garden To Reflect project that Bowman Riley Architects’ supported at Manorlands Hospice for Sue Ryder Care opened on 8 September 2014.</p>\r\n<p>Based in Oxenhope near Keighley, Manorlands Hospice provides specialist palliative care and treatment at home, or in the hospice, for people and their families who are suffering from serious illnesses.</p>\r\n<p>Working with horticulturalists, Bowman Riley helped design the new garden on a pro-bono basis for provide a tranquil outdoor space for patients and their families to enjoy and to remember loved ones that have been lost.</p>\r\n<p>A team of six Bowman Riley staff took part in a volunteer day to help with all the planting to facilitate the completion of the garden.</p>\r\n<p>As part of the company’s Corporate Social Responsibility initiatives, Bowman Riley offers all staff the opportunity to take an annual paid volunteer day to participate in a community or charity project.</p>', 'Creating New Garden for Hospice', 'The Garden To Reflect project that Bowman Riley Architects’ supported at Manorlands Hospice for Sue Ryder Care opened on 8 September 2014.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'creating-new-garden-hospice', '', '', '2014-11-12 14:39:08', '2014-11-12 14:39:08', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=news&#038;p=402', 0, 'news', '', 0),
