(514, 1, '2014-10-30 11:16:02', '2014-10-30 11:16:02', '<h3>Autistic Care Development</h3>\r\n<p>Bowman Riley Healthcare was commissioned to design a new 24 bedroom autistic care development with communal facilities, car parking and landscaping to provide facilities for supported living for people with autism.</p>\r\n<p>Our design seeks to create a secure and welcoming development comprising a single storey six bedroom home and two four bedroom homes and a two storey apartment building with 10 flats. The emphasis was on creating a sense of place and a space that is intimate.</p>\r\n<p>The arrangements and massing of the buildings has been designed to minimise the impact on the surrounding neighbourhood. Corresponding with the triangular shape of the of the site, the buildings have been arranged with single storey bungalows to the south and east with the taller building located centrally. Hipped roofs reduce the skyline impact of the building and assist in visually stepping down towards the boundaries.</p>\r\n<p>Due to the nature of the building, inclusive access was of primary importance. The building has been designed to be accessible throughout for residents and visitors.</p>', 'Autism Care UK (part of the Maria Mallaband Care Group)', 'Bowman Riley Healthcare was commissioned to design a new 24 bedroom autistic care development with communal facilities, car parking and landscaping to provide facilities for supported living for people with autism.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'autism-care-uk-part-maria-mallaband-care-group', '', '', '2014-10-30 11:16:02', '2014-10-30 11:16:02', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=casestudies&#038;p=514', 0, 'casestudies', '', 0),
(515, 1, '2014-10-30 11:15:58', '2014-10-30 11:15:58', '', 'Autistic-Care-Development', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'autistic-care-development', '', '', '2014-10-30 11:15:58', '2014-10-30 11:15:58', '', 514, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Autistic-Care-Development.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(516, 1, '2014-10-30 11:17:51', '2014-10-30 11:17:51', '<h3>Buckingham House Care Home</h3>\r\n<p>Bowman Riley Healthcare was commissioned to develop the designs for a new luxurious residential care home to accommodate 53 older people in a conservation area within the village of Gerrards Cross.</p>\r\n<p>The new residence provides residential, nursing and dementia care on the site of a redundant public house that had been closed since 2007.</p>\r\n<p>The design incorporates three distinct design elements. The south-eastern block reflects the design of the former public house building whilst the north-western block mirrors the traditional local vernacular. A modern glazed element links the two, with a large modern element to the rear of the buildings. The result is that the building appears to have developed organically on site.</p>\r\n<p>There are several listed buildings in the vicinity of the site and it was important that the new building does not detract from the conservation area setting.</p>\r\n<p>The design was produced using Building Information Modelling (BIM) and Revit Architecture. The use of BIM helped develop the complex scheme considering the unusually shaped site and the restrictions placed its redevelopment.</p>', 'Maria Mallaband Care Group', 'Bowman Riley Healthcare was commissioned to develop the designs for a new luxurious residential care home to accommodate 53 older people in a conservation area within the village of Gerrards Cross.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'maria-mallaband-care-group-2', '', '', '2014-11-11 14:11:31', '2014-11-11 14:11:31', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=casestudies&#038;p=516', 0, 'casestudies', '', 0),
