(525, 1, '2014-10-30 11:28:19', '2014-10-30 11:28:19', '<h3>Orchard Croft Medical Centre</h3>\r\n<p>Bowman Riley Healthcare was commissioned by Orchard Croft Medical Centre through Solutions4Care under a traditional form of contract to design the extension of an existing medical facility in the town of Horbury, near Wakefield.</p>\r\n<p>Built in the 1970s, Orchard Croft Medical Centre had outgrown the existing building, which resulted in medical staff working in areas that were no longer fit for purpose.</p>\r\n<p>Bowman Riley designed new consulting rooms, additional clinical spaces and office accommodation to bring the premises up to meet Care Quality Commission standards.</p>\r\n<p>The challenge was to provide the new facilities to a limited capped public funding based on a set area agreed with the District Valuer.</p>\r\n<p>The complex development required a unique design to achieve the exact area ratio to comply with District Valuer standards. Building information modelling (BIM) and Revit Architecture was adopted for this project, which added value in terms of aiding the planning process and stakeholder understanding through 3D visualisations and helped ensure compliance with the District Valuer.</p>', 'Orchard Croft Medical Centre', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'orchard-croft-medical-centre', '', '', '2014-11-11 12:49:42', '2014-11-11 12:49:42', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=casestudies&#038;p=525', 0, 'casestudies', '', 0),
