(540, 1, '2014-10-30 12:11:30', '2014-10-30 12:11:30', '<h3>Bupa Cromwell Hospital</h3>\n<p>Bowman Riley Architects was commissioned to design the internal refurbishment of four floors of Bupa Cromwell Hospital, a renowned private hospital, based in central London, which opened in 1981 as a state-of-the-art private facility for complex medical procedures.</p>\n<p>To enhance the hospital’s reputation for excellence in patient care, Bupa needed to refurbish ward accommodation, consulting rooms, paediatric and ancillary accommodation to comply with the current best practice guidance on the design of healthcare facilities; Health Technical Memoranda (HTMs) and Health Building Notes (HBN).</p>\n<p>Working with the main contractor, Bowman Riley is currently producing construction information to tight deadlines whilst the hospital is fully operational.</p>', 'Bradford NHS Foundation Trust', 'Bowman Riley Architects was commissioned to design the internal refurbishment of four floors of Bupa Cromwell Hospital, a renowned private hospital, based in central London, which opened in 1981 as a state-of-the-art private facility for complex medical procedures.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '538-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-10-30 12:11:30', '2014-10-30 12:11:30', '', 538, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/uncategorized/538-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(541, 1, '2014-10-30 12:58:55', '2014-10-30 12:58:55', '<h3>Catheter Laboratory, Bradford Royal Infirmary</h3>\r\n<p>Bowman Riley Healthcare was commissioned to design a new 300m² catheter laboratory and refurbishment of existing cardiac ward at Bradford Royal Infirmary to provide state-of-the-art facilities for patients with heart problems.</p>\r\n<p>The new cardiac unit will be among the most advanced of its kind in the country and will provide a dedicated x-ray laboratory and day-case unit for cardiac procedures.</p>\r\n<p>The establishment of the new unit will also ensure that more patients will be treated in Bradford, rather than having to travel to the regional cardiac centre at Leeds General Infirmary.</p>\r\n<p>The Foundation Trust anticipates that the new lab will treat more than 1,000 patients a year.</p>\r\n<p>The single storey purpose designed building will provide a modern, bright and comfortable medical environment situated within a central courtyard surrounded by existing clinical wards.</p>\r\n<p>It is anticipated that the new facility will lead to increased capacity, greater efficiency and more privacy for patients, as patients will not have to be transferred through public areas of the hospital.</p>', 'Bradford NHS Foundation Trust', 'Bowman Riley Healthcare was commissioned to design a new 300m² catheter laboratory and refurbishment of existing cardiac ward at Bradford Royal Infirmary to provide state-of-the-art facilities for patients with heart problems.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'bradford-nhs-foundation-trust', '', '', '2014-10-30 12:58:55', '2014-10-30 12:58:55', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=casestudies&#038;p=541', 0, 'casestudies', '', 0),
(542, 1, '2014-10-30 12:58:44', '2014-10-30 12:58:44', '', 'Catheter-Laboratory-Bradford-Royal-Infirmary-1200', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'catheter-laboratory-bradford-royal-infirmary-1200', '', '', '2014-10-30 12:58:44', '2014-10-30 12:58:44', '', 541, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Catheter-Laboratory-Bradford-Royal-Infirmary-1200.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(543, 1, '2014-10-30 13:00:38', '2014-10-30 13:00:38', '<h3>Emergency Ward Reconfiguration, Medway Maritime Hospital</h3>\r\n<p>Bowman Riley Healthcare is providing architectural and lead consultant services for the redevelopment of the Medway Maritime Hospital’s Emergency Department.</p>\r\n<p>Medway NHS Foundation Trust was one of 14 healthcare trusts in the UK identified by Sir Bruce Keogh in 2013, as demonstrating persistently high mortality rates. Subsequent visits by bodies including the Care Quality Commission identified the Emergency Department, as one of the key areas that needed urgent attention to bring the department in line with current best practice guidelines.</p>\r\n<p>Bringing our extensive experience of acute healthcare, we are working with the Trust to meet a challenging timetable of deadlines to reconfigure the emergency ward. Our team is using Building Information Modelling (BIM) to bring the benefits of increased accuracy and efficiency to the project.</p>', 'Medway NHS Foundation Trust', 'Bowman Riley Healthcare is providing architectural and lead consultant services for the redevelopment of the Medway Maritime Hospital’s Emergency Department.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'medway-nhs-foundation-trust', '', '', '2014-10-30 13:00:38', '2014-10-30 13:00:38', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=casestudies&#038;p=543', 0, 'casestudies', '', 0),
