(689, 1, '2014-11-06 15:04:40', '2014-11-06 15:04:40', '<h3>Leslie Silver Building</h3>\r\n<p>Bowman Riley Architects designed the prestigious Leslie Silver Building, which provides the gateway to Leeds Beckett University’s City Campus from Woodhouse Lane. The landmark building is named after Leslie Silver OBE, former Chancellor of the University and former chairman of Leeds United football club.</p>\r\n<p>Working closely with the University, we carefully designed the new building to house the city campus library, one of the University’s most impressive libraries across five floors providing information resources and learning support facilities 24 hours a day, seven days a week throughout the year. The fully integrated information resource facility for students, staff and visitors provides quiet study areas and group study areas, 350 open access networked PCs and a high specification multi-media editing suite.</p>\r\n<p>The low levels of energy consumption and consequent low carbon emissions make the Leslie Silver Building a significantly energy efficient building. The lighting is a highly sophisticated system controlled by presence sensors. The building has a state of the art air conditioning system, which recycles warm air, to ensure that the building engineering systems are kept operating at optimum levels a BMS system monitors the building and relays the information to the university’s energy manager.</p>\r\n', 'Leeds Beckett University', 'Leslie Silver Building', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'leeds-beckett-university-2', '', '', '2014-11-12 10:29:08', '2014-11-12 10:29:08', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=casestudies&#038;p=689', 0, 'casestudies', '', 0),
(690, 1, '2014-11-06 15:04:35', '2014-11-06 15:04:35', '', 'Leeds-Beckett-University-Leslie-Silver', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'leeds-beckett-university-leslie-silver', '', '', '2014-11-06 15:04:35', '2014-11-06 15:04:35', '', 689, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Leeds-Beckett-University-Leslie-Silver.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(691, 1, '2014-11-06 15:06:43', '2014-11-06 15:06:43', '<h3>School of Life Sciences</h3>\r\n<p>At the University of Bradford, the School of Life Sciences has the highest number of students of all of the schools, with more than 2,000 students admitted to a variety of courses in the areas of Biomedical Sciences, Chemical and Forensic Science, Clinical Sciences, Optometry, Pharmacy and Archaeological, Geographical and Environmental Sciences.</p>\r\n<p>Bowman Riley Architects designed and project managed the first phase of a £4.3million major refurbishment of the School of Life Sciences involving the modernisation of the biomedical science laboratories, the forensic enhancement suite, clinical skills and aseptic suites.</p>\r\n<p>The development incorporate integrated learning, state of the art technology and high quality AV interactive simulation equipment.</p>\r\n<p>The first phase of this prestigious development has been successfully delivered and has set the quality and standards for the later stages to create a world class teaching facility.</p>', 'University of Bradford', 'At the University of Bradford, the School of Life Sciences has the highest number of students of all of the schools, with more than 2,000 students admitted to a variety of courses in the areas of Biomedical Sciences, Chemical and Forensic Science, Clinical Sciences, Optometry, Pharmacy and Archaeological, Geographical and Environmental Sciences.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'university-bradford', '', '', '2014-11-06 15:06:58', '2014-11-06 15:06:58', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=casestudies&#038;p=691', 0, 'casestudies', '', 0),
(692, 1, '2014-11-06 15:06:37', '2014-11-06 15:06:37', '', 'School-of-Life-Sciences', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'school-of-life-sciences', '', '', '2014-11-06 15:06:37', '2014-11-06 15:06:37', '', 691, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/School-of-Life-Sciences.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(693, 1, '2014-11-06 15:08:54', '2014-11-06 15:08:54', '<h3>Harrogate Sixth Form Pavilion</h3>\r\n<p>Harrogate Grammar School, an independent academy trust, is a specialist Language and Technology College in Harrogate with 1,700 pupils, of which 400 pupils are in the sixth form.</p>\r\n<p>To accommodate the school’s ever expanding further education 16-19 section, Bowman Riley Architects was commissioned directly by the School to design and provide CDM coordination on a new £2 million Sixth Form Pavilion to replace temporary classrooms.</p>\r\n<p>The new Pavilion provides purpose-built, world-class facilities for the students to learn, succeed and be prepared to take the next step into higher education or employment.</p>\r\n<p>All sixth form facilities are now housed together on one site that contains well-equipped teaching classrooms, supervised areas for independent study, spaces for students to work collaboratively, laboratories, social spaces and a cloister garden. The laboratories are specifically for sixth form use and are fully equipped for the study of all three sciences at advanced level.</p>\r\n<p>The Forum is a lecture theatre with retractable seating of 300, which provides a focal point for the academic work of the school and accommodates a variety of events including conferences, open days and student performances.</p>\r\n<p>Harrogate Grammar School is proud of their outstanding sixth form facilities, which are matched by the outstanding achievements of their students.</p>', 'Harrogate Grammar School', 'Harrogate Grammar School, an independent academy trust, is a specialist Language and Technology College in Harrogate with 1,700 pupils, of which 400 pupils are in the sixth form.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'harrogate-grammar-school', '', '', '2014-11-06 15:08:54', '2014-11-06 15:08:54', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=casestudies&#038;p=693', 0, 'casestudies', '', 0),
