(731, 1, '2014-11-07 10:59:51', '2014-11-07 10:59:51', '<h1>Positive contribution</h1>\r\n<p class="p1"><span class="s1">CSR covers all our efforts to make a positive contribution to our clients, partners and suppliers, to the communities in which we work, to the lives of our own people, and to the environment.  Our CSR policy addresses key areas of responsibility:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class="p1">To create positive working environments where our people are happy and motivated to be the best they can be</li>\r\n<li class="p1">To undertake business fairly and with integrity</li>\r\n<li class="p1">To contribute positively to the communities in which we work</li>\r\n<li class="p1">To protect the environment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class="p1">Our people</h3>\r\n<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Our success as a company depends on the commitment of our people and on the support that we give them.</span></p>\r\n<h3 class="p1">Our business</h3>\r\n<p class="p1"><span class="s1">We are committed to acting honestly and fairly in all our dealings with our clients, suppliers and partners.</span></p>\r\n<h3 class="p1">Our communities</h3>\r\n<p class="p1"><span class="s1">We are committed to ensuring that the impact we have on the communities where we live and work is as positive as possible.</span></p>\r\n<h3 class="p1">Our environment</h3>\r\n<p class="p1"><span class="s1">We understand the environmental impacts the construction industry has on our world and we are fully committed to promoting sustainable designs and to manage our own workplaces as sustainably as possible.</span></p>\r\n<p><a href="http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/CSR-logos.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-335" src="http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/CSR-logos.jpg" alt="CSR-logos" width="300" height="70" /></a></p>', 'Our CSR', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '14-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-11-07 10:59:51', '2014-11-07 10:59:51', '', 14, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/uncategorized/14-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(732, 1, '2014-11-07 11:02:30', '2014-11-07 11:02:30', '<h1>Sketchbook</h1>\r\n<p>Lorem Ipsum is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry. Lorem Ipsum has been the industry''s standard dummy text ever since the 1500s, when an unknown printer took a galley of type and scrambled it to make a type specimen book. It has survived not only five centuries, but also the leap into electronic typesetting, remaining essentially unchanged. It was popularised in the 1960s with the release of Letraset sheets containing Lorem Ipsum passages, and more recently with desktop publishing software like Aldus PageMaker including versions of Lorem Ipsum.</p>', 'Sketchbook', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '250-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-11-07 11:02:30', '2014-11-07 11:02:30', '', 250, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/uncategorized/250-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(733, 1, '2014-11-07 11:10:24', '2014-11-07 11:10:24', '<h1>Our Story</h1>\r\n<p>In 1968 three architects decided to launch a new practice and unable to decide on where to locate the Head Office to best serve the commercial centres of Leeds and Manchester, a pin was stuck in a map somewhere in between. The market town Skipton, on the edge of the Yorkshire Dales was picked and there our story began.</p>\r\n<p>From the beginning the practice has had a very clear, unswerving, focus on quality design, attention to detail and client care, so much so that we continue to work with long standing clients, some of whom span back to our company’s inception.</p>\r\n<p>Today Bowman Riley is a dynamic and commercial practice led by directors Darren Bush, John Coultas, Michael Feather, Matthew Jones and Laurence Teeney operating from offices in Leeds, London and Skipton. To complement our design services, we offer a range of Building Consultancy services led by Robin Holme.</p>\r\n<p>In 2010 Steve Batson and Mark Dean joined our family and launched Bowman Riley Healthcare Architects to meet the needs of this specialist market.</p>', 'Our Story', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '6-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-11-07 11:10:24', '2014-11-07 11:10:24', '', 6, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/uncategorized/6-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(734, 1, '2014-11-07 11:10:44', '2014-11-07 11:10:44', '<h1>Our Story</h1>\r\n<p>In 1968 three architects decided to launch a new practice and unable to decide on where to locate the Head Office to best serve the commercial centres of Leeds and Manchester, a pin was stuck in a map somewhere in between. The market town Skipton, on the edge of the Yorkshire Dales was picked and there our story began.</p>\r\n<p>From the beginning the practice has had a very clear, unswerving, focus on quality design, attention to detail and client care, so much so that we continue to work with long standing clients, some of whom span back to our company’s inception.</p>\r\n<p>Today Bowman Riley is a dynamic and commercial practice led by directors Darren Bush, John Coultas, Michael Feather, Matthew Jones and Laurence Teeney operating from offices in Leeds, London and Skipton. To complement our design services, we offer a range of Building Consultancy services led by Robin Holme.</p>\r\n<p>In 2010 Steve Batson and Mark Dean joined our family and launched Bowman Riley Healthcare Architects to meet the needs of this specialist market.</p>', 'Our Story', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '6-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-11-07 11:10:44', '2014-11-07 11:10:44', '', 6, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/uncategorized/6-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
